CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 24, 1957, pg. B7 reads: "Dignitaries Of The ABA - shown here are, left to right, Allan L. Woolridge, Washington; Victor Daly, president, Washington; Georgia Stevens, Detroit, executive secretary; Kermit Ross, treasurer, Washington, and Dr. P.M. Goode, Mobile, Ala., executive board chairman."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Allan L. Woolridge, Victor Daly, Georgia Stevens, Kermit Ross, and Dr. P.M. Goode, posed in Fort Pitt Hotel for the 24th annual American Bridge Association tournament
